review_blob: I liked this. It almost tasted more like a stout than an ipax, which was interesting. Bitter but very malty and roasty. I dont sense the citrus too much until the end but still enjoyed it
beer_name: Grand Teton Trout Hop Black IPA

review_blob: I do taste the apple and pear that they claim in the deScription, which adds a pleasant tartness to the beer. I cant say I love it or that its a complicated beer, but this one makes for a good session type beer. Not as spicy as a normal saison, but lacks the complexity and the deep belgian yeast flavors. Almost tastes like it had flavors added afterward to a relatively sterile base.

Cant say I liked it. It resembles the style, but feels very thin for something that is called a strong, dark ale. Tastes boozy, but isnt particularly strong in any other flavors. A bit medicinal and flat, hints of butterscotch. Almost no bitterneess. Ive liked other things from lonerider, especially their seasonals, but this one was a dud for me.
beer_name: Lonerider Raleigh Beer Week Belgian Strong

review_blob: A bit malty with a faint bitterness at the finish. Mild licorice aftertaste which I didnt expect at all. Not very happy but fairly smooth. Wouldnt seek it out but wouldnt reject it either

Given to me as a gift which is very fitting for a Christmas beer. Very dark and incredibly boozy. Having with dinner so tastes are getting mixed up but its a nice strong beer if it is cold outside. I still prefer the normal offerings from the brewery thoigh. Thick head and lots of lace, thick as all hell

This was a delightful little brew. Tropical was a good name for it, but Ill admit I was skeptical. The citrus is very noticeable and varied. I can taste all forms of citrus in this one, so it lives up to its name. Strong like an IPA, but different enough that it is less bitter while still having good hop character. Not piny, but a bit of resin. Enough to keep the beer from being unbalanced. This could be a great go-to if it were available year round. Light mouthfeel makes it even more "session"
beer_name: Boulevard Collaboration No. 5 Tropical Pale Ale

review_blob: Been awhile since my last rate. Gotta get that palate back in shape. Very rich coffee flavor. Not disappointed. This almost takes like a coffee that had beer added to it. A bit bitter with some mild butterscotch flavors. Didnt realize how strong it was until I read the label. Great buy for 4.50 bomber

Bought and held onto by a personal recommendation from a friend, this is one of my first 5 or so sours, so my palate might not be well tuned for this. It really opened up with warmth and had more tannins at the bottom of the bottle as well. Really quite sour, more than the others Ive had so far. I enjoyed the sparkling feel to it also, which gave it a "flavored soda" kinda experience to it. The cherries come out well, but were a bit subdued while the beer was cold. All in all, a good sour I guess? I enjoyed it, but I probably cant rate it properly. I enjoyed Caractere Rouge more for the same price.
I am too sleepy to write anything real about this. It was as it promised. A hoppy monster that I could taste even through my stuffy nose. Sickly pale this time though.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Calling IPA

review_blob: Shame I had a bit of a stuffy nose tonight. This one was nice and hoppy, which was a surprise. The cascade hops are probably to blame. Really sweet also though. Gonna keep this one short. I liked it
beer_name: Bear Republic Big Bear Black Stout

review_blob: I havent liked a scotch ale before, and I guess this one isnt going to make me start craving the style, but it had some things I enjoyed about its flavors. Its almost a butterscotch flavor, but I know that is the wrong way to describe it. Interesting, but still didnt really like it

This one has a cool nose that I cant quite explain. It has a sweet molasses and caramel flavor that I am used to , but also a roastiness that I havent seen before. Its cool to have a unique flavor like that. The beer itself otherwise isnt something Id seek out again but was pleasant enough. Nitro tap
UPDATED: APR 7, 2015
beer_name: Two Brothers Bare Tree Weiss Wine (2002 and later)

review_blob: I remember not liking the original siberian night, but it;s been awhile. I do like this though. Really deep roastiness that fades a little bit to malty sweetness as the beer warms. Tannin mouthfeel from the barrel is noticeable. Not really capable of finding nuances tonight, but I do like this versus the first siberian night i had
beer_name: Thirsty Dog Bourbon Barrel Aged Siberian Night

review_blob: The scotch flavor is pretty noticeable especially when warmer but not necessarily strong. It would be better if the beer was better. A bit watery and flat. Not too much going on. Like a barrel aged heineken. Smell cedary. A little tart
This beer was just delightful. Great for this new years eve. It feels a bit streamlined, kinda like leffe which was bought by inbev. Very boozy. Nutty with sweet caramel as well
Definitely doesnt taste German but very obviously at wheat beer. A bit tart but very sessionable.
Tastes really bubble gummy. Like a bazooka. A bit boozy once warmed up. Smells of caramel and grapes. Really sweet. Not amazing and isnt super dynamic but still pleasant
beer_name: Lost Coast 25th Silver Anniversary Belgian Ale

review_blob: I ended up liking this beer. Strong is an understatement. If I have more than one, I am spending the night lol Reddish tinge was a nice touch. Both the cherries and honey are noticeable. I actually enjoyed this one quite a bit... very fitting for the season. Smells very sweet, but captures that belgian taste like I love despite it being called an american strong ale. Fizzy, strong boozy mouthfeel and almost no bitterness.
beer_name: Tregs The Mad Elf Holiday Ale

review_blob: Seems Ive sort of moves away from the arrogant bastard flavor lately. Maybe because its cold? Very strong beer. It really tastes like arrogant basyard with more octane , but the base flavors arent much stronger to compensate for higher abv. Bitterness is strong though abd it actually is more potent but not better than normal ab

I can definitely notice the house flavor here. This is the base of the caractere rouge. Sour with some plum and grape raisin flavors. Sweetness at the end is surprising. Great middle ground of sour and normal beer. Barrel tannins adds a depth to the tongue feel abd are more noticeable in the nose
High quality ipa here. Fairly dank but definitely an east coast style. Very bitter as well for the abv. Otherwise normal

This one grew on me very slowly. I had to drink it three times before I actually liked it. The pumpkin spice flavor is agreeable but tastes very artificial as well. Almost like a kids drink. Has a nice chestnut flavor from the malts though. Glad I tried it but wont get again probably. Spicy though which was cool with a stout
Leaves a very thick lace. Not quite as heavy as a celebrator. Still a good flavor. Dont know enough about the style to compare to others.

That vanilla is so interesting. Very prominent which takes the ordinarily boring porter flavor to a good level. The malt profile itself isnt that great, but some licorice can be found. Not a bad booze level either. Pretty drinkable high abv beer
beer_name: Double Barley Thrilla in Vanilla Porter

review_blob: Pretty good. I might like more than Sierra Nevada. Hops are more pronounced and piney. Better than the first time I had it. Tastes strong for a normal pale

Tastes more like a pumpkin spice cake than a beer. That being said it tastes like a good pumpkin spice cake haha. A bit of yeasty breafiness but not Mich else besides the pumpkin. Succeed s at least in that regard
beer_name: Carolina Beer Co. Cottonwood Pumpkin Spiced Ale

review_blob: A bit toasty, but not too sweet. I didnt expect it to be that roasted. A bit like a maple bacon pretzel. A bit of a weird after taste like a hot dog to me. Looks like a pepsi

I dont see any of the unfiltered yeast while on tap. A bit sour and almost salsa/tomato flavored. Prominent corn flavor as well. Almost like chips and salsa. Light but also lacking flavor as a result. This is a harsh rating but would be bad to sip on at a party

This one lives up to the hype 100%. Big is not an understatement. I feel like I am drinking coffee that turns into beer as you leave it in your mouth. Everything is done well. Begins with the most roast Ive had in a stout. I dont know if its Oakes or not but has those elements. Hops are present and a bit spicy but the beer is not bitter. dark chocolate as well.

Pretty dark for a Saison. I can tell it?s a Belgian style but definitely not Belgian. I wouldn?t immediately place it as a Saison either. Very bready and a bit sweet at the beginning. Fruity middle which was unexpected. A bit of grape and medium spice. Decent beer but also unremarkable

These beers always have a gimmicky flavor. This one is a bit peppery and had some herbal flavors almost like basil. Not sure they entirely fit but the beer is interesting. A bit sweet and some spice but missed that essential Belgian flavor I like in a dubbel
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #4 - Valar Morghulis

review_blob: Sandpaper colored and very clear. Has lagunitas distinctive house flavor but has great bitterness that finishes strong. Hoppy but not boozy or spicy. I am not in love with pilseners but I do love lags house flavor so its balanced out

An explosion of grape upon first taste. I prefer this flavor to the raisin that is commonly found in these types of beer. The fruit tastes more alive. Strong caramel nose with secondary licorice Boozuness is obvious and not recessed. Very sweet though with almost no bitterness. You can tell it s not a barley wine because the hop flavor doesnt really exist much here. I like that about it though. Malt purity

Didnt really care for this one much, but its also been awhile since my last English style beer. Tasted very bready, but also reminded me greatly if yuengling. Thats a mixed feeling because I feel like the beer should be better as a craft brew, but it has the session potential like a yuebgling. Has a bit of tart.

A world of difference from the Tank 7, which I found good but not great. This is something special that I enjoyed a lot. Head for days and lace that will never fade... Super thick. Murky but not sedimented. Having the dank with the saison yeast is something really special to me. I am not used to that dry hop character in a saison normally, but it fits so well with this beer. Definitely worth the hype. One of my new favorites.

Better than I expected but not exactly unique in any way to me. This is going to be a short review, and I will just let the numbers do the talking. Had a cool minty type flavor... A little bit like indian paan that I wasnt expecting, but was nice. Other than that, just a high quality, generic IS.

Estery just like I like it. I am having trouble finding the barrel flavor except for quick bits that taste mildly and a bit of tannin tartness but I can tell differences from the normal tripel. Super bready while cold which fades to more sweet as it warms. Almost a pilsener level of bread. Which works really well with the banana Belgian flavors. Very good tripel but not worth the 16 for the bottle.
UPDATED: JUL 11, 2014

I appreciate the breadiness. Not as aromatic as Id have expected. A bit of a light doppelbock in color and flavor. Malt sweetness that has a peak mid taste with a small bit of spice. Medium yeast with a strongly dominant bread flavor. Very minimal bitterness. Id buy this if it were on sale near me but the sweetness was both good and detracting from it
UPDATED: JUN 13, 2014

Had on tap as well as a bottle. One thing I like about this beer is that the Belgian yeast survives the High abv which is something I really appreciate. a bit fruity without being citrus like a pale ale. Alcohol warms but does not burn. Caramel Sweet from start to finish

First barley wine in a long time at the brass tap on draft. Such caramel sweetness with hop balance. I miss this style. Mildly dank with some licorice. Not boozy at all. Not as good as Bigfoot but a great reintroduction. Reddish brown with mild lace

Bought it as a joke but it turned out pretty good. Nice and spicy. Rather bitter than what I expected. Quite fruity tartbess but not really citrusy. I like ommegang s yeast profile as usual..very bready.. The numbers speak for the rest.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #3 - Fire and Blood

review_blob: Hazy amber color with heavy sedimentation. Very malty which is noticeable from the very beginning. Yeast flavor doesnt emerge until beer warms up butonce it does is very smooth. Caramel sweetness and fresh bread dominate the aroma. This us one if the beers that has more complexity in the flavor than the nose. A bit of hop bitterness and booze burn in the middle. Finished sweet and yeasty. Good beer and not God tier thoigh

Now this is what I am talking about. This beer is everything I like about stouts. Each breakfast flavor promised can be easily found and savored. Smells like brown chocolate and cappucino. i found the oats in there as well. No head in my bottle at all though. I could smell that cinnamon all day. Mild roastiness to allow for the chocolate to come through.

Really opened up with temperature. The barrel and scotch flavors were hard to spot but opened up later. As a new scotch drinker, I appreciate those notes. It seems this is more of a porter than a stout, and unfortunately, I feel that porters are just worse stouts. Chocolatey nose Licorice sweetness, no roast, and a slightly spicy mouthfeel despite no carbonation or head, which was pretty cool. Dark as night color.

On tap on 4/12 for the 420 dated beer. This one delivers on the hype for me. Better than hopslam. One of if not the best smelling hoppy beers Ive had. It feels like my nose is inside a pine tree. Dank and mossy. Its bitterness is almost like being salty like ocean water. Interesting touch. Doesnt really carry the stone house flavor as much as I thought but delivers in other ways.Sour notes of Orange citrus immediately after the barnyard middle flavors. Burns the mouth more than expected in a good way. Hard to drink quickly. stayed carbonated abd laced the whole time

If Im honest, this is the first letdown from the unibroue beers that I have tried. Maybe its the bottle I got? No head at all. Had a bit of an underwhelming mouthfeel and the taste felt like it took awhile to kick in with each sip. Didnt taste strong. Some lemony citrus that I found that was pretty cool, but all around this is the weakest unibroue so far. Still decent, but worse than the others I will rerate with another bottle whenever

This was good, but not as good as I expected. Boozy for sure, but the malty characters Ive come to expect from I stouts was a bit subdued imo. Maybe my nose could be a little bit less stuffy though. Nothing really defining that I can find, but a pretty well rounded brew, albeit underwhelming at times. I will have to try again sometime
